data.enText: work that is done as preparation for other work that will be done later

data.chText: 官员们正在为世界首脑峰会做准备工作。
data.enText: Officials are laying the groundwork for a summit conference of world leaders.

tr: preliminary preparation as a basis or foundation
example: we are prepared today because of groundwork that was done ten years ago
it was built on a base of solid rock
he stood at the foot of the tower

tr: the fundamental assumptions from which something is begun or developed or calculated or explained
example: the whole argument rested on a basis of conjecture

value.def: The groundwork for something is the early work on it which forms the basis for further work.

example.ex: Yesterday's meeting was to lay the groundwork for the task ahead...
example.tran: 昨天的会议是为以后的工作做准备。

example.ex: These courses provide the groundwork of statistical theory.
example.tran: 这些课程介绍的是统计学理论的基础。
